<HEAD>Lopez Rega, Notorious Cabinet Minister in Peron Government, Dead</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUENOS AIRES, Argentina (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Jose </PERSON> <PERSON> Lopez </PERSON> <PERSON> Rega </PERSON>, a police corporal and amateur astrologer who rose to power after he became President <PERSON> Juan </PERSON> <PERSON> Domingo </PERSON> <PERSON> Peron </PERSON>'s personal secretary, died in jail of a heart attack. He was 72. <PERSON> Lopez </PERSON> <PERSON> Rega </PERSON>'s death was announced Friday night by Judge <PERSON> Martin </PERSON> <PERSON> Irurzun </PERSON>'s office. The son of <LOCATION> Spanish </LOCATION> immigrants, <PERSON> Lopez </PERSON> <PERSON> Rega </PERSON> was born Oct. 17, 1916, in <LOCATION> Buenos </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Aires </LOCATION>. He tried a singing career and then became a policeman before being employed as a bodyguard for <PERSON> Peron </PERSON>, who was elected president in 1946 and then overthrown in a military coup in 1955. <PERSON> Lopez </PERSON> <PERSON> Rega </PERSON> renewed his acquaintance with <PERSON> Peron </PERSON> in the mid 1960s when the ousted leader was living in exile in <LOCATION> Madrid </LOCATION>. He became <PERSON> Peron </PERSON>'s personal secretary and returned to <LOCATION> Argentina </LOCATION> with <PERSON> Peron </PERSON> after the military dictatorship agreed to free elections. <PERSON> Peron </PERSON> was elected president in 1973 and he appointed <PERSON> Lopez </PERSON> <PERSON> Rega </PERSON> the minister of social welfare. <PERSON> Peron </PERSON> died July 1, 1974, and his wife, <PERSON> Isabel </PERSON>, who was vice president, became chief executive. <PERSON> Lopez </PERSON> <PERSON> Rega </PERSON> was a key adviser to her and gained wealth and power. Critics claim he helped set up the Argentine <ORGANIZATION> Anti-Communist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Alliance </ORGANIZATION>, a rightist death-squad organization accused of dozens of killings. <PERSON> Isabel </PERSON> <PERSON> Peron </PERSON> was ousted by an armed forces coup in 1976 and <PERSON> Lopez </PERSON> <PERSON> Rega </PERSON> fled <LOCATION> Argentina </LOCATION> and went into hiding. He was arrested in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and extradited to <LOCATION> Argentina </LOCATION> in July 1986 to face charges of fraud and conspiracy. Earlier this year he was acquitted of fraud but remained in jail pending trial on charges stemming from his alleged connection to the Anti-Communist Alliance.
