<HEAD>Big Bucks Likely to Characterize Races for Pepper, Wright, Coelho
Seats</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MIKE ROBINSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Millions of dollars of special interest money is expected to prime the political pumps as Republicans battle for three historically <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> seats in races spawned by the congressional ethics wars and the death of <PERSON> Claude </PERSON> <PERSON> Pepper </PERSON>. `` You're going to see candidates in all of these races spending a good deal of time trying to squeeze money out of the lobbyists, and there's no doubt that millions of dollars special interest funds will pour in,'' says <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Waldman </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Watch </ORGANIZATION>, a citizens group based here. The stakes are not momentous, since Democrats control the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION>, 259 to 175, and even a Republican sweep would not change things much. For that matter, registered Democrats predominate in all three districts. But Republicans lost face in April with special-election defeats in <LOCATION> Alabama </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Indiana </LOCATION>, even though they held on in <LOCATION> Wyoming </LOCATION>. They want to avenge those losses in the upcoming round. Democrats, on the other hand, want to avoid the embarrassment of an upset. The three districts are: _ The 12th District of <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, taking in much of <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Worth </LOCATION> <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Wright </PERSON>, who has represented it since 1955, stepped down as House Speaker on May 31 at the end of a yearlong ethics probe and is expected to resign from the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> itself by the end of the month. _ The 15th District of <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>, in the rich cotton, fruit and vegetable-growing <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Joaquin </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION>, the nation's premier center of agribusiness House Majority Whip <PERSON> Tony </PERSON> <PERSON> Coelho </PERSON>, who represented th