<HEAD>Republicans Aren't Pinning Hopes on Wright Seat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> officials are playing down their chances for Rep. <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Wright </PERSON>'s 12th District seat despite an ethics investigation that forced the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> Speaker to resign. `` It's like running the 100-yard dash between a Republican and a Democrat, and giving the Democrat an 80-yard head start,'' said <PERSON> Brian </PERSON> <PERSON> Epstein </PERSON>, a <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> political consultant in <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Worth </LOCATION>. `` It's not a fair race.'' Republican officials point to several factors in their decision to focus their efforts elsewhere. The district, which includes all of <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Worth </LOCATION> and most of its surrounding communities, was drawn by <PERSON> Wright </PERSON> himself. It is full of blue-collar Democrats and boasts a solid bloc of minority voters that averages 30 percent to 40 percent of the voter turnout. In addition, <PERSON> Wright </PERSON> brought home more defense contracts, jobs and federal funding than any other large urban area in the country received, according to a computer study earlier this year by The Dallas Morning News. Many residents view <PERSON> Wright </PERSON> as a martyr in an unjust political war. And two of the strongest of possible <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> candidates, <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Worth </LOCATION> Mayor <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Bolen </PERSON> and Tarrant County Judge Roy English, have indicated they are not interested in the seat. Finally, state Sen. <PERSON> Hugh </PERSON> <PERSON> Parmer </PERSON>, a formidable Democrat and longtime friend of <PERSON> Wright </PERSON>, is considered a viable candidate. <PERSON> Ed </PERSON> <PERSON> Rollins </PERSON>, deputy chairman of the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <OR